properties.title: Unified Saint John Housing Co-op Ltd.
properties.description: A group of eight small housing co-operatives in Saint John that merged to form the Unified Saint John Housing Co-operative in January 2016. These eight co‑ops were developed through a number of funding programs between 1981 and 1985 and included City Centre, Heatherway, High Meadow Park, Jenny’s Spring, Lower Cove, North End Family, South City, and Wright Street Housing Co‑ops.

properties.title: Rehabitat Inc.
properties.description: With over 100 units, Rehabitat apartments have a reputation of being affordable and attractive. A variety of buildings throughout Saint John and surrounding area, offer people a comfortable home. From non-elderly single people to seniors to families of various sizes, Rehabitat fulfils the mandate of providing safe, affordable housing that meet local demographics.
properties.address:
75 Adelaide St
Saint John, NB
Canada E2K 1W4

properties.title: Abbey St. Andrew
properties.description: A beautiful addition to uptown Saint John, the interesting architectural designs ensure that despite its size, “The Abbey” blends into the existing neighbourhood. One, two and three bedroom apartments are available with a variety of floorplans-some have dens, others have dishwashers, others have private decks. Convenient living at its best, all units enjoy in-floor heating and convenient garbage removal. Some units have dens, patios, dishwashers or stackable laundry facilities-all have access to laundry facilities. Underground parking is available.
properties.address: 181 Charlotte St, Saint John, NB E2L 0C7, Canada

properties.title: Rotary Admiral Beatty Complex
properties.description: Located on Douglas Avenue, St. Peter’s Non-Profit Housing is comprised of four family units and 20 senior housing apartments. On the busline, off-street parking, and proximity to shopping and local amenities makes this an easy place to live out retirement. A few families complete the community adding diversity to the mix.
properties.address: 18 King Square S #10, Saint John, NB E2L 1E5, Canada

properties.title: Harbourside Apartments
properties.description: Harbourside Apartments were constructed in 1984 as part of the Market Square Development Project. Harbourside allows residents to enjoy a superb waterfront location which is linked to the Market Square Complex, Canada Games Aquatic Centre, City Hall, Brunswick Square, City Market, Brunswick House, Mercantile Centre, as well as Harbour Station.
properties.address: 55 Smythe St, Saint John, NB E2L 5A2, Canada

properties.title: Leinster Court
properties.description: Saint John Non Profit Housing Inc. is proud to be part of this unique development. Completed in 2008 and situated in a prime area of the city centre near all amenities, Leinster Court offers upscale living for a variety of residents. The 52 unit complex consists of 24 2-bedroom suites, 21 1-bedroom suites and 7 mobility suites.
properties.address: 53-91 Leinster St, Saint John, NB E2L 1J1, Canada

properties.title: Bicentennial Court
properties.description: Bicentennial Court is the inaugural project of Saint John Non Profit Housing Inc., and contains a total of 17 units of family accommodation located in two blocks connected by an overhead walkway.

Saint John, NB E2L 5A6

properties.title: Presland Mews
properties.description: Presland Mews is located at 200-208 Presland Road and was completed in 1987.æ This is our flagship property and we are proud to say that we have been home to families for almost 30 years at this location!

properties.title: Communityworks Place
properties.description: Communityworks Place was completed in 1989 and consists of 45 1 & 2 bedroom units, including 6 modified units.
properties.address: 1370 Ogilvie Road Ottawa, ON K1K 4P1, Canada

properties.title: Paterson Walk
properties.description: Paterson walk was completed in 1990.  A 23 unit four storey walk up building, the project has on-site laundry facilities, a balcony with each unit and surface parking.  This innovative development was OntarioÍs first multi-storey multi-unit apartment building to be manufactured inside a factory and transferred to site.  The $1.8 million project boasted a standard of construction unusual in wood-frame building because the components were manufactured in ideal interior conditions, the quality of the structure was superior to most site-built wood-frame buildings.

properties.title: Cliff House
properties.description: This development has a seven story concrete apartment building with 20 stacked townhouses, two elevators, laundry facilities and a balcony for each unit.

This building has an elevator, laundry facilities and mail delivery to the building.

properties.title: MacTier and District Community Housing
properties.description: Located in the hamlet of MacTier, this 20 unit apartment building provides one, two and three bedroom units to families, seniors and singles. The units are equipped with fridge and stove. Two one-bedroom accessible units for physically disabled. The building offers a mix of rent-geared-to-income and market rent units. There is a common room and laundry facilities.
